# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1916-brooklyn-robins-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1876 Chicago White Stockings season** was the fifth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the first in the National League and the third at 23rd Street Grounds.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings, as one of the founding members of the new National League, won the NL's initial championship during this season with a record of 52–14.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] The **1877 Boston Red Caps season** was the seventh season of the franchise.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] Arthur Soden became the new owner of the franchise, who won their first National League pennant.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The **1878 Boston Red Caps season** was the eighth season of the franchise.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The Red Caps won their second straight National League pennant.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1879-providence-grays-season] The **1879 Providence Grays** won the National League title in only their second season in the league.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1880-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1880 Chicago White Stockings season** was the ninth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the fifth in the National League and the third at Lakefront Park.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1880-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 67–17.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1881-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1881 Chicago White Stockings season** was the tenth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the sixth in the National League and the fourth at Lakefront Park.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1881-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 56–28.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1882-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1882 Chicago White Stockings season** was the 11th season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the seventh in the National League and the fifth at Lakefront Park.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1882-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 55–29, 3 games ahead of the second place Providence Grays.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1916-brooklyn-robins-season] The **1916 Brooklyn Robins** won their first National League pennant in 16 years and advanced to the first World Series in franchise history, where they lost to Babe Ruth and the Boston Red Sox in five games.
[src:1916-brooklyn-robins-season/1916-brooklyn-robins-season] Note: Rube Marquard was team leader in saves with 5.
